Born June 11, 1917, in Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., to Joseph L. Wirthlin and Madeline Hither. Sustained as Assistant to the Quorum of the Twelve April 4, 1975, at age 57; sustained to the First Quorum of the Seventy Oct. 1, 1976, and called to the Presidency of the Seventy Aug. 28,1986; sustained to the Quorum of the Twelve Oct. 4, 1986, and ordained an apostle Oct. 9, 1986, at age 69; died Dec.1, 2008, at Salt Lake City, Utah, at age 91.

